node.text:
NEW WAYS TO PAINT WITH KIDS 🎨• New and Unique Art Experiences for your Toddlers, Preschoolers and Big kids! ••••••••••• Tap that bookmark and save this list of ideas at the end for when you need them. I’ve scrolled waaaaaayyyy back in my feed for you and there are 25 awesome ways to paint that my kids and I have loved. My personal faves are painting with sponges and pom poms 🤗 No surprise there! 😉 Painting can be a beneficial experience for our children for so many reasons! Give them the chance to get messy, creative, and experience new materials 👉👉 Which ones will you try at home? Make sure to tag friends who might benefit from this list as well 👇🥰 
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
🐛 CATERPILLAR COLORS 🌈• Fill the colorful circles of the caterpillar! This color matching and fine motor activity has an easy setup - trace around a cup or bowl in each color to create your caterpillar. Provide dot markers or stickers for your toddler to dot and match colors. Save this one to try later! Leave a comment, tag a friend and let me know if you’ll try this at home 🥰👇Happy Tuesday!

.
.
.
.

node.text:
🍎 APPLE STAMP TREES 🌳🍂 One of our favorite ways to paint is with half an apple as a stamp! Apple stamping is a classic art project for preschoolers and this is a fun way to take it a bit further and use the stamps to make a seasonal fall tree as autumn approaches! 🤗🍂🌳 Inspo: @crafty_morning blog ••••••• Setup: Cut an apple in half and set out with paints. Draw a tree with branches on a large roll of paper. Encourage dipping + stamping the apples to make a tree full of autumn colors or simply make a green tree 🌳 if you have plenty of summer left ahead! 👉👉 Will you try this one at home?! Tag a friend who might love this fall project as well👇🥰 and don’t forget to bookmark the post for September! 
.
.
.
.
.
.
